cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as disease name recognition and classification using recurrent neural network models.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes end-to-end models for the NLP tasks, which involve training neural networks to learn features and make predictions.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing intelligent systems for NLP tasks using deep learning techniques.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes recurrent neural network models for the NLP tasks, which are a type of neural network.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with information retrieval tasks, but the disease name recognition and classification tasks can be seen as related to information extraction and organization.
